WEBVTT

00:06.767 --> 00:09.800
Alone and adrift in a big city.

00:09.800 --> 00:12.633
Anna would want me to take you
in hand.

00:12.633 --> 00:14.333
DAVID:
Mummy! Mummy! Come see!

00:14.333 --> 00:16.533
GEORGIE:
Come on! Granny's pretty!

00:16.533 --> 00:17.900
Granny looks great!

00:17.900 --> 00:19.267
-DAVID: Quick!
-SARAH: Shabbat.

00:19.267 --> 00:21.733
I would be thrilled if you come,

00:21.733 --> 00:24.067
but only if you're
truly comfortable with it.

00:24.067 --> 00:27.100
One never knows
unless one tries.

00:27.100 --> 00:29.200
SARAH:
Happiness is my enemy.

00:29.200 --> 00:31.133
How do you say
you've made my dreams come true

00:31.133 --> 00:32.867
and that terrifies me?

00:33.400 --> 00:34.767
Just like that.

00:34.767 --> 00:36.600
But I have to stop running
from us.

00:36.600 --> 00:38.167
No more fear.

00:38.700 --> 00:40.200
I can do it.

00:40.200 --> 00:41.700
I've been thinking.

00:41.700 --> 00:42.900
How would you like it?

00:42.900 --> 00:44.000
Sell?

00:44.000 --> 00:45.500
I've offered it to Harry.

00:45.500 --> 00:47.433
I reckon I can snag him a loan
through Missy.

00:47.433 --> 00:49.533
ANNA: I need to follow through
on the new film deal

00:49.533 --> 00:51.400
with Burbank National Pictures.

00:51.400 --> 00:52.400
They're in town.

00:52.400 --> 00:54.667
Just wear a wedding ring
at least.

00:54.667 --> 00:58.700
You will be viewed as cheap
and your child a bastard.

00:58.700 --> 01:00.467
They need to know sometime.

01:00.467 --> 01:04.066
A community clinic, mine to run,
totally independently.

01:05.167 --> 01:07.100
What do you think?

01:07.100 --> 01:09.600
Social medicine's on the rise.
Jack may make it work.

01:09.600 --> 01:12.067
Well, that's for me to judge.

01:12.067 --> 01:13.867
It won't.

01:13.867 --> 01:15.867
That stays in this room.

01:15.867 --> 01:17.200
Shove your offer.

01:17.200 --> 01:20.433
Don't add to your woes
by making trouble!

01:20.967 --> 01:23.533
For the first time,
I think we might not make it.

01:25.733 --> 01:27.667
Goodbye.

01:27.667 --> 01:30.067
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

01:32.833 --> 01:35.167
Certainly! Go on!

01:35.167 --> 01:38.300
[ Clock ticking ]

01:38.300 --> 01:41.500
Yes, they're out there getting
his mother's car now.

01:41.500 --> 01:42.767
She'll never marry him.

01:42.767 --> 01:45.167
For seven years,
she's been saying she will.

01:45.167 --> 01:47.400
That's why she won't.

01:48.500 --> 01:50.567
She'll never marry anyone.

01:50.567 --> 01:52.933
[ Dramatic music plays ]

01:54.000 --> 02:00.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:02.467 --> 02:04.667
Mark's just proposed to Julia,

02:04.667 --> 02:07.533
but Jacqueline still holds
a torch for him.

02:07.533 --> 02:08.800
Mm!

02:08.800 --> 02:11.167
There I was thinking my life's
in turmoil.

02:11.167 --> 02:13.400
Mama.

02:14.333 --> 02:17.533
Hopefully by this afternoon
I'll have some wonderful news.

02:19.600 --> 02:21.700
You're going to be sensible,
aren't you?

02:23.067 --> 02:26.500
I'm going to be me.

02:26.500 --> 02:29.067
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

02:32.567 --> 02:36.267
[ Indistinct conversations,
glasses clinking ]

02:39.467 --> 02:41.067
[ Door opens ]

02:41.600 --> 02:43.533
-Terry.
-Ah! How are you?

02:43.533 --> 02:45.367
Just over here.

02:45.367 --> 02:46.533
Good.
I'm not late.

02:46.533 --> 02:48.200
-[ Laughs ]
-[ Laughs ]

02:48.200 --> 02:49.500
They're delayed.

02:49.500 --> 02:51.700
It gives us time to prepare.

02:52.333 --> 02:54.667
Oh, what on earth?

02:55.533 --> 02:57.367
Four and a half months.

02:57.367 --> 03:01.700
Ah.
And...no husband?

03:01.700 --> 03:04.067
Not a hint of one.

03:04.067 --> 03:06.900
-You should have said something.
-Show and tell.

03:06.900 --> 03:08.733
This is utterly irresponsible.

03:08.733 --> 03:11.067
I think we both need a drink.

03:11.067 --> 03:13.267
You could have at least dressed
to conceal.

03:13.267 --> 03:14.867
It'll come out eventually.

03:14.867 --> 03:16.967
When the ink's dry.

03:16.967 --> 03:18.633
[ Sighs ]
Thank God they're late.

03:18.633 --> 03:20.200
Marielle is around the corner.

03:20.200 --> 03:22.433
Buy yourself something capacious
quickly.

03:22.433 --> 03:23.800
[ Laughing ]
Why?

03:23.800 --> 03:26.367
Dry martini, olive.
Thank you.

03:26.367 --> 03:27.933
And you'd better make hers
a double.

03:27.933 --> 03:30.333
It's off
if they see you like that.

03:30.333 --> 03:31.567
Why?

03:31.567 --> 03:33.267
-Why?
-Yes.

03:33.267 --> 03:36.067
You know as well as I do.

03:36.067 --> 03:39.067
Oh, you'll give marvelous
interviews looking like that.

03:39.067 --> 03:40.733
And photos?

03:40.733 --> 03:42.600
Miss Anna Bligh?

03:42.600 --> 03:44.433
Look what happened to Bergman
with Rossellini,

03:44.433 --> 03:47.133
and she's one of the world's
biggest stars.

03:47.133 --> 03:48.900
Hollywood is conservative.

03:48.900 --> 03:51.533
They won't touch an unwed mother
with a barge pole.

03:51.533 --> 03:52.700
-Let's see.
-Anna --

03:52.700 --> 03:54.267
You're presuming.

03:54.267 --> 03:56.167
I'm prepared to take a risk.

03:56.167 --> 03:58.300
Indulge me.

04:00.200 --> 04:03.067
You're prepared to risk this?

04:05.133 --> 04:06.933
That's what you'll be losing.

04:06.933 --> 04:08.267
Goodness.
They are keen.

04:08.267 --> 04:11.900
That buys a lot of security
for you and your child.

04:12.933 --> 04:14.900
Someone has to draw a line
in the sand.

04:14.900 --> 04:16.700
But not today.

04:16.700 --> 04:17.867
[ Door opens ]

04:17.867 --> 04:19.300
-Oh!
-What?

04:20.067 --> 04:21.600
-Ah. Yes, sir.
-Hi.

04:21.600 --> 04:23.267
Looks like we'll see,
doesn't it?

04:23.267 --> 04:24.767
Mm.

04:24.767 --> 04:26.100
They might surprise.

04:26.100 --> 04:28.633
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

04:28.633 --> 04:30.467
Gentlemen.

04:31.333 --> 04:33.700
[ Indistinct conversations ]

05:01.167 --> 05:04.233
The grog's arrived.
How many are you expecting?

05:04.233 --> 05:06.067
I'm determined we don't run dry.

05:06.067 --> 05:07.233
So it seems.

05:07.233 --> 05:08.533
You've cleared the budget?

05:08.533 --> 05:10.800
What James doesn't know
won't hurt him.

05:10.800 --> 05:12.700
You've been sorely missed.

05:13.267 --> 05:14.867
Look at these.

05:14.867 --> 05:17.333
It puts the "wa-wa"
into "boudoir."

05:17.333 --> 05:18.467
[ Laughter ]

05:18.467 --> 05:19.467
You like?

05:19.467 --> 05:21.300
Oh, I love.

05:21.300 --> 05:23.267
I'll be touting them
around the party.

05:23.267 --> 05:25.100
If you don't get
more commissions,

05:25.100 --> 05:26.833
it won't be my fault.

05:26.833 --> 05:30.900
Oh, the old pile
is coming alive.

05:31.367 --> 05:33.067
And I don't mean me.

05:33.067 --> 05:35.733
[ Laughter ]

05:35.733 --> 05:38.100
Oh, look.
Our guest is settling in.

05:38.100 --> 05:41.133
Oh, he's an adorable boy.
I'll let him know you're here.

05:43.733 --> 05:46.067
How exactly did Henry happen?

05:46.067 --> 05:48.367
He came thinking Elizabeth
was still here,

05:48.367 --> 05:50.933
and Prudence harangued him
into staying --

05:50.933 --> 05:53.800
at least until after
his operation.

05:53.800 --> 05:55.667
The old pile is coming alive.

05:55.667 --> 05:57.167
And you do mean her.

05:57.167 --> 05:58.767
[ Both laugh ]

06:00.433 --> 06:02.067
So?

06:02.700 --> 06:03.967
So?

06:04.667 --> 06:07.067
That too-forced smile.

06:07.067 --> 06:08.200
What's beneath?

06:11.133 --> 06:13.267
[ Sighs ]

06:13.267 --> 06:17.067
What could he have said that
wouldn't have shattered you?

06:17.067 --> 06:21.600
Anything that indicated a notion
of change.

06:21.600 --> 06:24.467
He's being dumped
after years of dedication

06:24.467 --> 06:28.633
and his answer is to stay fixed
in a different guise.

06:28.633 --> 06:31.567
He could have found
a new hospital,

06:31.567 --> 06:32.767
improved his credentials,

06:32.767 --> 06:34.933
even taken a break
to consider his options.

06:34.933 --> 06:38.433
But he goes back
to the man who's ousting him

06:38.433 --> 06:39.600
and floats a plan

06:39.600 --> 06:43.600
to be little more
than a GP-cum-social worker.

06:43.600 --> 06:45.867
He sees it as nobly motivated,

06:45.867 --> 06:48.767
but it just shows how blinkered
his horizons are.

06:48.767 --> 06:50.867
Say it to him, not me.

06:50.867 --> 06:52.333
[ Sighs ]

06:52.333 --> 06:55.167
We'd be on the same merry-go-
round we've been on for years.

06:56.200 --> 06:59.733
'Round and 'round,
settling nothing.

07:00.767 --> 07:04.400
But you've been living
with things as they are.

07:04.400 --> 07:07.600
You have this wonderful new job.

07:07.600 --> 07:09.267
What's changed?

07:09.267 --> 07:12.433
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

07:12.433 --> 07:15.067
I had a glimpse
of something new.

07:17.833 --> 07:19.833
I didn't truly realize
until then

07:19.833 --> 07:24.767
how...desperately I wanted it,

07:24.767 --> 07:28.233
not just a compromise patch
over the wound.

07:28.233 --> 07:30.100
You love him.

07:32.367 --> 07:36.700
Which is why s-saying goodbye
broke my heart.

07:37.300 --> 07:39.100
He knows?

07:39.100 --> 07:42.133
I'm too much of a coward.

07:42.133 --> 07:44.767
But I knew as I left Ash Park...

07:46.400 --> 07:48.267
...then it's over.

07:49.667 --> 07:52.667
We'll die with a whimper,
not a bang.

07:55.333 --> 07:58.333
It all sounds so bleak.

08:01.200 --> 08:02.800
For me.

08:03.733 --> 08:07.067
But if I do it well enough,
I can...

08:07.067 --> 08:09.333
minimize the pain for him.

08:15.100 --> 08:17.067
Having you helps.

08:18.800 --> 08:23.367
Having a friend I can talk to
honestly...

08:24.233 --> 08:26.367
...who I know can understand.

08:27.167 --> 08:29.067
I'll need it.

08:30.733 --> 08:33.600
Well, you know what I want.

08:34.167 --> 08:36.067
I'm not blind.

08:37.967 --> 08:42.200
But I will do nothing
until I know you're free.

08:45.100 --> 08:46.467
Thank you.

08:46.933 --> 08:50.167
For my own protection
perhaps as much as for yours.

08:52.533 --> 08:56.233
[ Telephone ringing
in distance ]

08:56.233 --> 08:59.267
[ Music continues ]

09:02.400 --> 09:04.067
Sir?
The telephone.

09:04.067 --> 09:05.533
Anna Bligh.

09:11.133 --> 09:13.100
Over there, sir.

09:13.567 --> 09:14.733
Ah.

09:17.800 --> 09:19.633
Henry, darling!

09:19.633 --> 09:21.467
Thank you.

09:22.100 --> 09:24.167
Come.
Commiserate.

09:24.167 --> 09:25.667
Are you sure you need more?

09:25.667 --> 09:27.367
Need?
No.

09:27.367 --> 09:30.100
Want?
Very much.

09:30.100 --> 09:32.100
Two!
Thank you.

09:32.100 --> 09:36.467
One for this gorgeous man
who I have treated so poorly.

09:36.467 --> 09:39.767
I just -- I wanted to get things
out of the way before we spoke,

09:39.767 --> 09:42.300
and, well,
out of the way they are.

09:44.067 --> 09:48.400
I've lost a rather large sum
of money.

09:48.400 --> 09:50.733
My publisher, too.

09:50.733 --> 09:54.500
Seems I am unseemly in the eyes
of Burbank National Pictures.

09:55.067 --> 09:57.533
Grand gestures
are not appreciated.

09:57.533 --> 10:00.800
I feel very noble
and very depressed.

10:00.800 --> 10:03.300
[ Exhales deeply ]
Start at the start.

10:03.300 --> 10:05.533
How are you?
Are you all right?

10:05.533 --> 10:09.833
I was so pleased to hear
that Prudence took you in.

10:09.833 --> 10:12.533
You first.
And only one more drink.

10:12.533 --> 10:15.000
[ Whispering ]
I'm a bit of a scandal.

10:16.033 --> 10:17.533
A lovable one.

10:18.067 --> 10:19.433
Go.

10:20.667 --> 10:22.333
Well...

10:22.900 --> 10:24.733
You have no intention
of marrying?

10:24.733 --> 10:26.467
No.

10:26.467 --> 10:28.100
I see.

10:28.700 --> 10:30.800
You understand the position
that puts us in.

10:31.367 --> 10:33.700
Can't my work speak for itself?

10:33.700 --> 10:36.733
Do you have to highlight me
in the process?

10:36.733 --> 10:39.000
Maybe not now, but if we pour
money into filming

10:39.000 --> 10:40.633
and this gets out...

10:40.633 --> 10:43.333
If you could guarantee
you'll be married by then.

10:43.333 --> 10:44.967
I don't see what difference
it makes.

10:44.967 --> 10:48.700
The film is the film,
and it is adult material.

10:48.700 --> 10:51.400
So are you --
unmarried, with a kid.

10:52.000 --> 10:53.800
That's too adult.

10:53.800 --> 10:55.467
This is a woman's picture,

10:55.467 --> 10:58.133
and women are
far more judgmental than men.

10:58.133 --> 11:00.267
STONE:
If we could get some guarantee.

11:00.267 --> 11:02.733
We like your work.
We want it.

11:02.733 --> 11:06.500
Come back to us married,
the deal stands.

11:06.500 --> 11:09.667
So I show the wedding
certificate, you show the check?

11:10.800 --> 11:12.567
That's about it.

11:14.733 --> 11:16.233
That's not why I'm here.

11:16.233 --> 11:18.700
Oh, no, my darling.

11:18.700 --> 11:19.767
Ah.

11:19.767 --> 11:23.667
I'm afraid I...lost my cool.

11:23.667 --> 11:25.867
This is such hypocrisy.

11:25.867 --> 11:27.867
We all know what goes on
in Hollywood.

11:27.867 --> 11:29.600
You flaunt stars
like two-dollar whores.

11:29.600 --> 11:32.333
But perish the thought
a woman makes an adult choice

11:32.333 --> 11:33.733
to raise a child on her own.

11:33.733 --> 11:35.200
-Well, then the heavens fall.
-Enough!

11:35.200 --> 11:39.067
I will not marry to satisfy
your double standard.

11:39.067 --> 11:42.633
If that sees me out of pocket,
fine.

11:45.067 --> 11:46.733
And it certainly does.

11:46.733 --> 11:49.567
I've never seen so many zeroes
in my life.

11:49.567 --> 11:51.933
[ Down-tempo music playing ]

11:56.567 --> 11:58.167
I don't know what you think
you're doing.

11:59.067 --> 12:00.967
You're a talented author.

12:00.967 --> 12:03.933
It saddens me
to see you implode.

12:05.200 --> 12:06.600
What, that's it?

12:06.600 --> 12:09.433
Well, the other studios
will feel exactly the same.

12:12.367 --> 12:15.667
I can't imagine what you think
you've achieved.

12:17.767 --> 12:19.867
[ Silverware clanking
in distance ]

12:19.867 --> 12:22.300
And...what do you think
you've achieved?

12:24.067 --> 12:27.233
At least I know now
what my work's worth.

12:27.233 --> 12:28.733
Nothing.

12:29.333 --> 12:31.067
Something.

12:32.067 --> 12:33.467
Everything.

12:35.067 --> 12:36.267
What?

12:36.267 --> 12:41.200
I'll raise our baby, unmarried,
head held high.

12:47.933 --> 12:49.967
[ Grunts ]

12:50.933 --> 12:52.967
Thought you'd want the honors.

12:53.433 --> 12:55.733
I like to think she's watching.

12:55.733 --> 12:57.600
I'd say she is.

12:59.700 --> 13:02.567
Now let's see what response
this gets.

13:05.200 --> 13:07.133
[ Vehicle approaching ]

13:07.133 --> 13:09.533
It's called testing the waters.

13:09.533 --> 13:12.067
Blokes.
Talkin'.

13:12.067 --> 13:13.567
Well, stranger things
have happened.

13:13.567 --> 13:15.567
Mm.

13:15.567 --> 13:16.567
Pass them around.

13:16.567 --> 13:18.600
SARAH:
Good afternoon, gentlemen.

13:19.067 --> 13:21.400
I'm chief recruiting officer.

13:21.400 --> 13:23.233
What do you reckon?

13:23.233 --> 13:26.700
She was a pillar of the
community, so it's very fitting.

13:27.167 --> 13:29.433
Always say the right thing, eh?

13:30.867 --> 13:32.733
I'll do me darndest for you.

13:33.600 --> 13:35.333
Shouldn't you be at home?

13:35.333 --> 13:37.067
I'm collecting my things.

13:41.500 --> 13:43.367
I could have brought them.

13:46.600 --> 13:48.633
I needed the moment.

13:53.233 --> 13:55.300
I've had bits of myself
scattered around

13:55.300 --> 13:57.167
for six years now.

13:58.600 --> 14:01.400
Oh!
This is David's.

14:01.400 --> 14:03.433
[ Chuckles ]

14:04.833 --> 14:07.133
Keep it for the littlies.

14:10.467 --> 14:12.167
Quite a wrench.

14:13.633 --> 14:17.633
I've nursed
for my entire adult life.

14:18.267 --> 14:20.267
Must feel strange.

14:20.267 --> 14:21.867
Especially with what
you've got planned.

14:21.867 --> 14:23.900
I'd love to be a part of it.

14:24.467 --> 14:27.500
But I need to give Mrs. Bligh
a go.

14:28.867 --> 14:31.100
Elizabeth saw it as a job.

14:31.100 --> 14:33.067
Maybe that's the way
to approach it, you know?

14:33.067 --> 14:35.500
You're just carrying on working.

14:37.067 --> 14:38.833
I hope it's enough.

14:38.833 --> 14:40.333
Won't know till you try.

14:40.333 --> 14:42.067
I won't.

14:42.067 --> 14:44.367
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

14:46.400 --> 14:48.100
[ Sighs ]
I want to cry.

14:51.767 --> 14:53.233
Truth?

14:56.367 --> 14:58.067
So do I.

14:58.900 --> 15:01.167
[ Birds chirping ]

15:03.933 --> 15:05.933
SARAH:
Good boy.

15:05.933 --> 15:07.967
[ Music continues ]

15:09.600 --> 15:11.967
[ Clock ticking ]

15:22.533 --> 15:28.067
Baruch ata Adonai,
Eloheinu melech haolam,

15:28.067 --> 15:31.067
...asher kidishanu
bimitzvotav vetzivanu,

15:31.067 --> 15:33.467
l'hadlik ner shel Shabbat.

15:35.267 --> 15:36.600
Shabbat shalom.

15:36.667 --> 15:38.433
Shabbat shalom.

15:43.433 --> 15:45.733
-SARAH: Shabbat shalom.
-DAVID: Shabbat shalom.

15:50.067 --> 15:50.867
Yes.

15:51.633 --> 15:53.500
The done thing.

15:53.500 --> 15:55.833
[ Music continues ]

15:55.833 --> 15:57.433
Shabbat shalom.

15:57.500 --> 15:59.400
Shabbat shalom.

16:16.400 --> 16:18.600
-[ Knock on door ]
-Yeah?

16:19.800 --> 16:22.167
Doctor, before I head home,
may I?

16:22.167 --> 16:23.400
Make it quick.

16:23.400 --> 16:25.100
Indeed.

16:30.133 --> 16:32.667
There was confusion at the CWA.

16:32.667 --> 16:33.833
What might that be?

16:33.833 --> 16:35.833
Our women's clinic -- no more.

16:35.833 --> 16:38.800
What does it mean --
"men's groups"?

16:38.800 --> 16:41.833
Will this simply encourage them
to come together to complain

16:41.833 --> 16:44.600
against whatever comforts
you're offering their wives?

16:44.600 --> 16:46.133
Is that what the women
are saying?

16:46.133 --> 16:48.400
Well, it was their space.

16:48.400 --> 16:51.067
And it still will be.
"Us and them" doesn't help.

16:51.067 --> 16:53.967
We ladies and men
are not the same, Doctor.

16:53.967 --> 16:55.267
There is a divide.

16:55.267 --> 16:59.067
There was sanctuary, knowing
that the clinic was ours.

16:59.067 --> 17:01.367
Maybe the blokes need some space
too.

17:01.367 --> 17:03.533
They have the public bar.

17:03.533 --> 17:06.067
Booze and bombast, Doris.

17:07.067 --> 17:10.333
They might need a place
to talk their feelings.

17:10.333 --> 17:11.500
Men don't.

17:11.500 --> 17:12.733
Maybe they should.

17:12.733 --> 17:14.633
Maybe there wouldn't have been
a Stan O'Rourke

17:14.633 --> 17:17.666
if he'd had a place
to get it off his chest, hmm?

17:17.666 --> 17:20.532
[ Indistinct conversations
in distance ]

17:20.532 --> 17:21.567
Perhaps.

17:21.567 --> 17:24.700
I'll manage it
so we can all share.

17:24.700 --> 17:25.833
You think I wouldn't?

17:25.833 --> 17:28.467
If anything, it'll be better.

17:28.467 --> 17:29.400
How?

17:29.400 --> 17:31.467
That was for me to figure.

17:31.467 --> 17:33.300
For now, just accept the fact.

17:34.067 --> 17:35.700
I do.

17:39.900 --> 17:42.367
I shall be your emissary.

17:42.367 --> 17:44.067
I'd appreciate that.

17:44.067 --> 17:47.067
[ Indistinct conversations,
telephone ringing ]

17:48.367 --> 17:50.067
Sleep tight.

17:51.533 --> 17:54.067
Did you like it, Granny?

17:54.067 --> 17:57.333
Yes.
I did.

17:58.233 --> 17:59.567
Good night.

17:59.633 --> 18:01.233
Good night.

18:01.867 --> 18:03.533
Roll over now.

18:03.533 --> 18:06.567
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

18:13.633 --> 18:17.533
The house is still resting
firmly on its foundations.

18:19.600 --> 18:21.433
Sometimes fear needs fearing

18:21.433 --> 18:23.433
more than the things
that we fear.

18:33.933 --> 18:37.300
[ Insects chirping,
dog barking in distance ]

18:41.067 --> 18:43.433
CAROLYN:
It's a "be fabulous" party.

18:43.433 --> 18:47.233
Delia's not stinting,
but it's money well spent.

18:47.233 --> 18:49.767
She's invited the wealthy
of your old set

18:49.767 --> 18:51.300
and a smattering of mine.

18:51.300 --> 18:54.067
Needless to say, none would
get into Casa Swanson

18:54.067 --> 18:55.833
in the normal run of events.

18:55.833 --> 18:57.800
-How will Prudence cope?
-[ Laughs ]

18:57.800 --> 19:00.067
CAROLYN: She's revealing
her inner fag hag.

19:00.067 --> 19:02.300
[ Laughs ]
A monster is born.

19:02.300 --> 19:03.933
OLIVIA:
We miss you!

19:03.933 --> 19:05.733
JAMES:
Olivia says hello.

19:05.733 --> 19:08.967
Georgie's sleeping. She can't.
So we're sitting vigil.

19:08.967 --> 19:10.633
CAROLYN:
Glad she's there?

19:10.633 --> 19:12.467
She asks if we're happy
to have her.

19:12.467 --> 19:14.600
It's wonderful to be here.

19:14.600 --> 19:16.267
Madly!

19:16.267 --> 19:18.867
That's Uncle William.
Georgie's won a heart.

19:18.867 --> 19:20.333
Oh, I'm sure.

19:20.333 --> 19:22.567
Wish us well
for winning some later.

19:22.567 --> 19:24.067
JAMES:
I'm sure you will.

19:24.067 --> 19:25.067
Give my love.

19:25.067 --> 19:26.533
Anna sends her love.

19:26.533 --> 19:28.700
Sounds like Grandmother's car.

19:28.700 --> 19:31.400
Mother's just arrived.
She'll want a quick word.

19:31.400 --> 19:33.433
I'll hand you over
as soon as she comes in.

19:33.433 --> 19:35.267
Send them safely home.

19:35.267 --> 19:37.100
They'll be spoiled rotten.

19:37.100 --> 19:38.933
CAROLYN:
She deserves it.

19:39.767 --> 19:41.433
She's earned it.

19:41.433 --> 19:44.433
[ Mid-tempo music plays ]

19:44.433 --> 19:48.267
So all through here is going to
be a huge arch, Moroccan style.

19:55.567 --> 19:57.300
Oh!
There you are.

19:57.867 --> 19:59.267
No Elizabeth?

19:59.267 --> 20:02.533
She's using the rigors
of the drive home as her excuse.

20:02.533 --> 20:04.900
It's lucky
she's not still living here.

20:04.900 --> 20:06.600
She'd have no choice.

20:06.600 --> 20:08.000
CAROLYN:
I'm sure.

20:08.000 --> 20:11.533
PRUDENCE: Where does Delia find
such handsome men?

20:11.533 --> 20:16.067
Joint's positively creak
with the waiters at my soirees.

20:16.067 --> 20:17.433
I hope you approve.

20:17.433 --> 20:20.500
I shall write to my Andrew
and scandalize him.

20:20.500 --> 20:21.500
[ Laughs ]

20:21.500 --> 20:23.267
Ah.
There you are.

20:23.267 --> 20:25.233
I'm sure you approve.

20:25.233 --> 20:26.833
Gorgeous!

20:26.833 --> 20:28.767
Even before the guests arrive.

20:28.767 --> 20:30.833
Um, I forgot to mention
there may be an extra.

20:30.833 --> 20:32.833
-Oh, yes?
-He didn't commit.

20:32.833 --> 20:34.300
Do tell.

20:34.867 --> 20:36.800
Uh, Harry Polson.

20:36.800 --> 20:39.567
He was good to me
when I was low.

20:39.567 --> 20:42.233
Then fling the doors wide.

20:42.233 --> 20:43.333
Excuse me.

20:44.433 --> 20:45.800
Delia, dear!

20:45.800 --> 20:46.933
She's in her element.

20:46.933 --> 20:49.000
Alarmingly.

20:49.000 --> 20:50.500
How's Anna?

20:50.500 --> 20:54.200
Alternating between defiance
and deflation.

20:54.200 --> 20:56.300
I left her discussing it
with Mother.

20:56.300 --> 20:57.800
Elizabeth's there?

20:57.800 --> 20:59.867
Just now.

20:59.867 --> 21:01.433
Ah.
I'll be back.

21:08.233 --> 21:10.267
[ Hammer tapping ]

21:12.333 --> 21:14.400
No day of rest?

21:14.933 --> 21:17.200
-Mine soon.
-Indeed.

21:17.200 --> 21:18.900
Keeps me at it.

21:19.633 --> 21:22.300
Well, now the paperwork.

21:22.300 --> 21:23.667
You check it over.

21:23.667 --> 21:26.233
If it all makes sense,
then, uh, we'll get it started.

21:26.233 --> 21:27.767
You don't have to do this.

21:27.767 --> 21:29.633
-I want to.
-I know Sarah wants --

21:29.633 --> 21:32.067
I want to.

21:36.200 --> 21:39.867
Harry...it occurred to me
at our wedding

21:39.867 --> 21:43.133
that there you were,
bearing witness for a man who...

21:43.800 --> 21:47.133
...I'll admit it, was part
of treating you shabbily.

21:48.633 --> 21:50.533
You've shown dignity with James.

21:50.533 --> 21:54.567
You've been a good friend
for that alone.

21:55.067 --> 21:56.900
And yes, for Sarah.

21:56.900 --> 21:59.100
She's deeply fond of you.

22:00.267 --> 22:02.100
Means a lot.

22:02.667 --> 22:04.567
I'll put these up in the house.

22:04.567 --> 22:06.567
You get back to it.

22:06.567 --> 22:08.100
Thank you.

22:10.200 --> 22:13.367
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

22:13.367 --> 22:15.767
All work and no play.

22:15.767 --> 22:18.567
Even God took a break on Sunday.

22:20.867 --> 22:22.900
[ Horse snorts ]

22:24.633 --> 22:26.800
[ Birds chirping ]

22:40.633 --> 22:44.533
If you've been sent to fetch me,
your trip is wasted.

22:44.533 --> 22:47.500
If you've come for Anna, good.
She needs distraction.

22:47.500 --> 22:48.900
Uh, neither.

22:48.900 --> 22:51.967
Well, take her anyway.
She's in a funk.

22:52.767 --> 22:55.767
I'm glad you and she
are talking.

22:55.767 --> 22:57.667
Well, what did she say?

22:58.500 --> 23:03.100
Well, that you'll be mother and
father but not husband and wife.

23:03.100 --> 23:06.067
Not without its challenges,
I expect.

23:06.067 --> 23:07.567
The child will be loved.

23:08.200 --> 23:09.933
What's most important.

23:09.933 --> 23:11.667
And protected.

23:12.267 --> 23:14.300
That's not why I'm here.

23:15.533 --> 23:17.867
[ Vehicle approaching ]

23:17.867 --> 23:20.167
[ Door closes ]

23:20.167 --> 23:22.600
[ Footsteps approaching ]

23:22.600 --> 23:25.567
[ Indistinct talking on radio ]

23:28.200 --> 23:30.067
Well, you're a start.

23:30.667 --> 23:32.200
Just checking.

23:32.733 --> 23:34.100
Come in.

23:34.100 --> 23:36.567
Well, no one's going to open up
in front of a copper.

23:37.400 --> 23:39.267
What about the copper
opening up?

23:39.267 --> 23:41.333
[ Chuckles ]
Nah.

23:41.333 --> 23:43.767
Tough as old boots, me.
No need.

23:45.533 --> 23:47.067
Next time.

23:47.467 --> 23:48.933
If there is one.

23:48.933 --> 23:50.433
I'm in it for the long haul.

23:55.533 --> 23:56.867
Does Carolyn know?

23:56.867 --> 23:59.867
No.
And ideally, nor should Jack.

23:59.867 --> 24:02.433
You're the one best placed
to control it.

24:02.433 --> 24:04.267
[ Clock ticking ]

24:04.267 --> 24:06.733
Is Mr. Burton normally
so unpleasant?

24:07.967 --> 24:11.700
He has the surgeon's conviction
of always being right.

24:11.700 --> 24:13.400
In spades.

24:13.400 --> 24:15.067
Sir Richard is fueling it.

24:15.067 --> 24:17.700
Well, he couldn't resist
another thrust of the rapier.

24:17.700 --> 24:19.733
Can you talk to the board?

24:21.233 --> 24:22.233
No.

24:22.233 --> 24:23.533
Surely you must be able --

24:23.533 --> 24:27.567
Just weeks ago, I would have
sailed in guns ablaze.

24:27.567 --> 24:30.767
But only one person
can solve this -- Jack.

24:31.467 --> 24:34.200
Everyone's problems their own.

24:34.200 --> 24:35.400
You and Anna too.

24:36.500 --> 24:38.367
Make your choices
as best you can

24:38.367 --> 24:39.733
from the information available.

24:40.667 --> 24:43.800
That's all Jack requires --
a heads-up.

24:44.333 --> 24:46.333
Not just the outside
that's changed.

24:47.500 --> 24:50.800
You inform Jack,
and then I'll set the scene.

24:50.800 --> 24:53.067
[ Mid-tempo music plays ]

24:53.867 --> 24:56.567
[ Telephone ringing ]

25:00.300 --> 25:01.733
Hello?

25:02.633 --> 25:05.067
[ Music continues ]

25:12.300 --> 25:14.333
[ Engine starts ]

25:16.667 --> 25:19.933
Mr. Burton.
Elizabeth Goddard.

25:19.933 --> 25:22.667
Uh, might we meet
this afternoon?

25:25.233 --> 25:28.300
[ Footsteps approaching ]

25:29.833 --> 25:31.400
Uh, he's sound asleep.

25:31.400 --> 25:33.467
The, uh, ride wore him out.

25:33.467 --> 25:34.567
What's all this?

25:34.567 --> 25:36.700
I've been going through
the accounts.

25:36.700 --> 25:38.433
Well trained by Mother.

25:38.433 --> 25:41.067
I now have a degree
in household management.

25:41.067 --> 25:42.133
Ah.

25:42.133 --> 25:44.433
-We spend too much, you know.
-How so?

25:44.433 --> 25:46.833
Well, we could do with half
the staff.

25:46.833 --> 25:50.400
If I'm to be mother and wife,
I don't need waiting on,

25:50.400 --> 25:52.767
and I've offered help
in the kitchen.

25:52.767 --> 25:54.267
I bet that went down well.

25:54.267 --> 25:56.233
Yes.
Cook is very protective.

25:56.233 --> 25:58.633
-It's her domain.
-My home.

25:58.633 --> 26:00.833
Ah.
Total commitment.

26:00.833 --> 26:01.833
It's how I am.

26:01.833 --> 26:03.900
I had noticed.

26:03.900 --> 26:05.067
[ Chuckles ]

26:05.067 --> 26:08.333
I must say I'm surprised.

26:08.333 --> 26:09.633
Why?

26:09.633 --> 26:11.900
How you're embracing domesticity
so fully.

26:11.900 --> 26:13.867
A lot more besides.

26:13.867 --> 26:15.167
I can help with the books,

26:15.167 --> 26:18.067
I can school David if he doesn't
settle well at the local,

26:18.067 --> 26:19.800
and I'd like to do more
around the property.

26:19.800 --> 26:22.200
-I'm perfectly capable.
-I have no doubt.

26:22.200 --> 26:24.333
And we could do more
charitably --

26:24.333 --> 26:27.633
possibly a food service
for some of the older folks.

26:27.633 --> 26:29.500
And you're thinking
of culling staff?

26:29.500 --> 26:31.433
The way you're going,
we'll end up hiring.

26:31.433 --> 26:34.600
I want Ash Park to be more
than just the house on the hill.

26:34.600 --> 26:36.967
-It's our house on the hill.
-But let's bring it to earth.

26:36.967 --> 26:38.700
Let's make it matter.

26:38.700 --> 26:39.800
Anything you want.

26:39.800 --> 26:41.633
As long as you're fulfilled
and happy.

26:41.633 --> 26:42.733
I am.

26:42.733 --> 26:44.667
I will be.

26:45.200 --> 26:48.867
I might ask cook about what it
would take to do a food service.

26:49.667 --> 26:52.700
I'll make it seem like her idea.

26:52.700 --> 26:54.667
-You're learning!
-Ha!

26:54.667 --> 26:57.700
[ Clock ticking,
birds chirping ]

27:04.067 --> 27:07.867
Mildred, that Canberra number
again, please.

27:09.767 --> 27:12.067
Oh, thank you.

27:12.500 --> 27:14.667
[ Sizzling ]

27:17.400 --> 27:21.533
Agatha, I've been thinking about
leftovers.

27:21.533 --> 27:22.767
How so, ma'am?

27:22.767 --> 27:26.067
Well, I hate to see good food
going to waste.

27:26.067 --> 27:28.600
Mm.
Crying shame, I call it.

27:29.867 --> 27:32.567
Perhaps we could put our heads
together on it.

27:33.867 --> 27:37.833
No, no.
Uh, the idea, it appeals.

27:37.833 --> 27:40.233
The, uh, the timing's bad.

27:41.067 --> 27:44.967
Does a refusal now
preclude a yes later?

27:47.133 --> 27:49.167
Then you may hear from me.

27:49.167 --> 27:51.833
It depends on my wife.

27:51.833 --> 27:53.900
It could be months.

27:56.233 --> 27:57.067
No, no.

27:57.067 --> 27:59.133
I-I will tell her when...

28:00.067 --> 28:02.433
...if it's right.

28:05.067 --> 28:06.233
Good.

28:07.533 --> 28:10.233
[ Up-tempo music plays ]

28:15.167 --> 28:17.700
[ Indistinct conversations ]

28:29.267 --> 28:31.967
PRUDENCE: Doesn't everyone look
thrilled to be here?

28:31.967 --> 28:33.967
Oh, it's such a variety.

28:33.967 --> 28:37.167
Oh, I do hope some of my set
arrive soon.

28:37.167 --> 28:38.600
Oh! There's some now!
Hello!

28:38.600 --> 28:40.100
Hello.

28:40.667 --> 28:43.067
So most of these
are your old friends?

28:43.067 --> 28:44.300
Oh, still friends, really.

28:44.300 --> 28:46.967
We always look forward
to seeing each other.

28:46.967 --> 28:48.600
Such glamorous guests.

28:48.600 --> 28:51.333
[ Mid-tempo music playing ]

28:51.867 --> 28:54.933
Where have these people been
all my life?

28:56.200 --> 28:58.867
Who is that exotic creature
just arriving?

29:00.233 --> 29:02.267
CAROLYN:
I'm not sure.

29:02.267 --> 29:05.300
Bill. Bob. Bruce?

29:05.833 --> 29:06.833
A man?

29:06.833 --> 29:08.733
CAROLYN:
In a fabulous frock.

29:08.733 --> 29:12.600
And the way Delia's gushing,
with a house needing attention.

29:13.300 --> 29:16.067
The good thing
about a lot of this crowd --

29:16.067 --> 29:18.433
no children
to soak up the money.

29:18.433 --> 29:21.433
Perhaps it's best
Elizabeth did decline.

29:21.433 --> 29:23.067
I hope your gang
won't be too shocked.

29:23.067 --> 29:25.133
Oh, carefully chosen.

29:25.133 --> 29:28.767
[ Laughing ]

29:29.733 --> 29:31.933
I must bring out the cigarettes.

29:31.933 --> 29:32.967
Over there.

29:33.633 --> 29:35.567
They're sharing!

29:39.467 --> 29:42.067
Your education continues.

29:42.500 --> 29:44.767
[ Indistinct conversations ]

29:45.500 --> 29:47.067
Henry.

29:47.533 --> 29:48.867
You sent Hollywood packing

29:48.867 --> 29:51.233
and you're worried
about a gaggle of homosexuals?

29:51.233 --> 29:52.567
More like my tongue.

29:52.567 --> 29:55.233
I'm likely to fire away again
if they start on this.

29:55.233 --> 29:58.133
This could well be the least
judgmental reaction we'll get.

29:58.133 --> 30:00.133
Well, at least
it's going to be witty.

30:00.133 --> 30:01.300
With queens?

30:01.300 --> 30:03.300
[ Laughs ]

30:03.300 --> 30:05.000
You ready?

30:06.567 --> 30:08.467
As I'll ever be.

30:08.467 --> 30:10.500
Into the fray.

30:11.467 --> 30:14.167
[ Up-tempo music playing ]

30:22.600 --> 30:24.600
My sweets!

30:24.600 --> 30:26.667
Arriving together.

30:26.667 --> 30:28.000
Public statement?

30:28.000 --> 30:30.067
We won't lie if asked.

30:30.067 --> 30:32.700
It seems an afternoon
for honesty.

30:32.700 --> 30:33.667
Prudence?

30:33.667 --> 30:36.333
Her eyes are on approving
stalks.

30:37.200 --> 30:40.167
Oh!
Oh, welcome!

30:40.167 --> 30:41.333
And adieu!

30:41.333 --> 30:43.533
[ Laughs ]
Gorgeous!

30:43.533 --> 30:45.600
-This special smoking.
-Yes?

30:45.600 --> 30:47.133
I love it.
It's beautiful.

30:47.133 --> 30:49.367
-Oh.
-I had a small puff myself.

30:49.900 --> 30:52.400
I think perhaps discretion.

30:52.400 --> 30:54.633
[ Whispering ]
The garden or the Moroccan room.

30:54.633 --> 30:56.767
I'll spread the word.
Take over.

30:58.433 --> 31:00.100
Can I leave this to you?

31:00.100 --> 31:02.400
I promised I'd return.

31:02.400 --> 31:04.067
It's delicious.

31:04.067 --> 31:06.067
[ Chuckles ]

31:06.067 --> 31:08.067
And you were worried
about being the scandal.

31:08.067 --> 31:10.167
It does add perspective.

31:10.167 --> 31:11.933
They're like you were
with the Americans.

31:11.933 --> 31:13.500
Hmm?

31:13.500 --> 31:15.667
Well, thumbing their noses
at society.

31:15.667 --> 31:17.567
I mean,
what harm does it do anyone?

31:17.567 --> 31:18.633
What harm does that?

31:18.633 --> 31:21.067
PRUDENCE:
Oh, so priceless.

31:21.067 --> 31:23.367
It glistens all over the place.

31:23.367 --> 31:24.567
Is it an heirloom?

31:25.100 --> 31:27.900
Today Prudence,
tomorrow the world.

31:27.900 --> 31:29.067
We can but hope.

31:30.233 --> 31:31.900
-We are on welcoming duty.
-Mm.

31:31.900 --> 31:34.467
Uh, welcome!
Hello. Welcome.

31:34.467 --> 31:35.767
Delia is through there.

31:35.767 --> 31:37.467
Mervyn Peel and Stephen Black.

31:37.467 --> 31:38.500
Henry!

31:38.500 --> 31:40.367
Overtaxing your hand,
naughty boy.

31:40.367 --> 31:41.767
[ Chuckles ]

31:41.767 --> 31:43.667
-MERVYN: And, uh, you are?
-Anna Bligh.

31:45.200 --> 31:47.767
Not the?

31:47.767 --> 31:49.900
A famous girl, chum.
Trust you.

31:49.900 --> 31:52.733
Your book jacket says
you're single.

31:52.733 --> 31:54.067
I am.

31:54.067 --> 31:56.533
Feel free to congratulate
the father.

31:56.533 --> 31:57.900
Oh.
Well, is he here?

31:57.900 --> 31:59.100
Point him out.

32:04.533 --> 32:06.200
Slap me down with a feather.

32:06.200 --> 32:08.100
ANNA:
[ Laughs ]

32:08.100 --> 32:09.267
But not...

32:09.267 --> 32:10.767
No.

32:10.767 --> 32:13.700
Well, Fox, you fox.

32:13.700 --> 32:14.700
ANNA:
[ Laughs ]

32:14.700 --> 32:16.333
Too camp!

32:16.333 --> 32:18.367
HENRY:
[ Clears throat ]

32:20.800 --> 32:23.433
[ Both laugh ]

32:24.900 --> 32:27.600
Mr. Burton.
Come in.

32:30.533 --> 32:32.367
This is a courtesy call.

32:32.367 --> 32:34.633
I am aware of your history
with the board.

32:34.633 --> 32:36.900
History -- past tense.

32:36.900 --> 32:39.100
You're here to talk
to the future.

32:40.400 --> 32:42.600
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

32:44.467 --> 32:46.333
Speak openly.

32:50.333 --> 32:51.467
I'll leave you.

32:51.467 --> 32:53.100
I came to see you.

32:53.100 --> 32:54.900
But this is what you're getting.

32:54.900 --> 32:56.433
Excuse me.

33:02.800 --> 33:06.733
I thought Henry Fox knew what
side his bread's buttered on.

33:06.733 --> 33:08.700
You're an unpleasant prick,
aren't you?

33:09.600 --> 33:11.133
[ Chuckles ]
I think --

33:11.133 --> 33:13.300
You're not used to
the direct approach?

33:13.300 --> 33:14.900
That's the trouble
with you surgeons,

33:14.900 --> 33:16.200
especially the higher you go.

33:16.200 --> 33:18.067
There's no one to say no.

33:18.067 --> 33:19.133
Well, I am.

33:19.133 --> 33:21.367
-I think --
-Shut up and listen.

33:22.300 --> 33:25.333
I could handle you turning
a job interview into a coup.

33:25.333 --> 33:28.467
I could just deal
with your supercilious manner

33:28.467 --> 33:31.700
when I explained my view
of a shared future.

33:31.700 --> 33:34.367
But there is no way I'm standing
back and letting you play games

33:34.367 --> 33:36.600
with the patients
I've poured my life into.

33:36.600 --> 33:38.433
So you can give credence
to my idea,

33:38.433 --> 33:41.367
you can work with me
and respect it,

33:41.367 --> 33:43.500
-or you can piss off.
-I'm not listening to this.

33:43.500 --> 33:46.600
Give it a proper go...

33:46.600 --> 33:51.100
and I might -- repeat --
might -- revise my opinion

33:51.100 --> 33:53.267
you're a self-centered,
arrogant bastard.

33:53.267 --> 33:54.267
This is outrageous!

33:54.267 --> 33:56.367
What's outrageous
is you swanning in

33:56.367 --> 33:58.667
like some minor Machiavelli,

33:58.667 --> 34:02.133
manipulating my hospital
before you've even started.

34:02.900 --> 34:06.067
Any surgeon who puts his ego
ahead of his patients

34:06.067 --> 34:07.900
is a shit surgeon in my book.

34:07.900 --> 34:11.167
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

34:11.167 --> 34:12.667
Have we got a deal?

34:12.667 --> 34:14.733
We certainly have not.

34:14.733 --> 34:16.233
All right.

34:17.333 --> 34:19.199
Then here's how it goes.

34:19.967 --> 34:22.600
I've got an appointment
with the board tomorrow.

34:22.600 --> 34:25.266
Elizabeth and Henry are coming,

34:25.266 --> 34:27.632
and we're laying the whole thing
out in front of them.

34:27.632 --> 34:30.699
Henry is bringing
a talented young colleague

34:30.699 --> 34:34.500
and an offer of both
of their skills in lieu of you.

34:34.500 --> 34:37.132
There's no way we're letting you
loose on the place.

34:37.132 --> 34:38.632
A second-rate doctor,

34:38.632 --> 34:40.733
a fairy who can't operate,
and some ring-in?

34:40.733 --> 34:42.199
And she's yesterday's news.

34:42.199 --> 34:43.266
Are the staff?

34:45.367 --> 34:49.067
Either the board takes the deal
or it's a full walkout.

34:49.067 --> 34:50.100
They voted.

34:51.600 --> 34:53.467
Board won't risk that.

34:54.199 --> 34:57.633
Do you want it known you were
dropped by a country hospital?

34:58.500 --> 35:01.500
The great Neil Burton, rejected.

35:02.967 --> 35:05.833
I'd retire with my reputation
intact.

35:09.600 --> 35:11.467
Well...

35:12.467 --> 35:14.733
...perhaps I misjudged you.

35:15.867 --> 35:17.367
There is fire.

35:17.367 --> 35:19.700
When it comes to my patients.

35:19.700 --> 35:21.867
We perhaps could have worked
together.

35:21.867 --> 35:23.467
No hope now.

35:23.933 --> 35:25.300
No.

35:29.267 --> 35:30.967
Do I cancel the board meeting?

35:32.133 --> 35:36.133
Your hick hospital is welcome
to stay firmly in the past.

35:36.133 --> 35:38.700
And you're welcome
to bugger off.

35:38.700 --> 35:40.533
No wonder you listen
to Richard Bennett.

35:41.567 --> 35:44.267
Tell him to enjoy his seat
on the board

35:44.267 --> 35:46.100
while he's still got it.

35:53.367 --> 35:55.800
[ Music continues ]

36:05.700 --> 36:08.067
[ Door closes ]

36:15.300 --> 36:18.833
Remind me never to play poker
with you.

36:20.433 --> 36:22.867
I have never seen a hand bluffed
so well.

36:22.867 --> 36:24.633
Well, now I'd better
actually get Henry

36:24.633 --> 36:26.067
and some whiz kid on board

36:26.067 --> 36:28.067
and I'll have myself a hospital
and a clinic.

36:28.067 --> 36:29.400
Mine.

36:33.433 --> 36:34.767
[ Rattling ]

36:34.767 --> 36:35.867
SARAH:
Four.

36:35.867 --> 36:37.667
One, two, three, four.

36:37.667 --> 36:39.167
Your turn.

36:39.167 --> 36:41.367
[ Rattling ]

36:43.100 --> 36:44.100
[ Gasps ]

36:44.100 --> 36:45.833
-Three!
-Three!

36:45.833 --> 36:47.767
One, two, three.

36:47.767 --> 36:49.733
-Who's winning?
-I am!

36:49.733 --> 36:50.933
I'm going to win.

36:50.933 --> 36:52.600
No, you're not.

36:52.600 --> 36:55.600
Cook's just baked a cake.
Fresh out of the oven.

36:55.600 --> 36:57.267
Why don't you go and get some?

36:57.267 --> 36:59.167
I have to talk to Mummy.

37:01.300 --> 37:04.100
That didn't take
too much prompting.

37:04.100 --> 37:05.100
What is it?

37:05.100 --> 37:06.367
Don't worry.

37:06.367 --> 37:08.900
It's, uh, it's nothing serious.

37:09.400 --> 37:11.300
I'd made a choice
not to tell you something,

37:11.300 --> 37:13.500
and I suddenly realized
that that was wrong.

37:14.833 --> 37:16.800
I didn't want to throw a spanner
in the works.

37:16.800 --> 37:19.167
You're trying so hard here.

37:19.167 --> 37:21.133
But I think you should know.

37:21.767 --> 37:22.733
Yes?

37:24.933 --> 37:28.333
I've been contacted
by the Israeli Embassy.

37:28.333 --> 37:31.433
My time in Canberra,
your history,

37:31.433 --> 37:34.367
our time on the kibbutz, David.

37:34.367 --> 37:37.200
If I'm agreeable,
they'll ask Menzies to add me

37:37.200 --> 37:39.233
to our diplomatic staff
in Israel.

37:40.733 --> 37:44.467
They want someone who can see
the complexities as they are.

37:45.233 --> 37:46.667
They want you to --

37:46.667 --> 37:48.167
Us.

37:48.167 --> 37:50.300
You too.

37:50.967 --> 37:53.733
You're very much part of it.

37:55.233 --> 37:57.700
Just as you're embracing this.

37:59.333 --> 38:02.433
But it's wrong
that we don't decide together.

38:03.400 --> 38:04.633
How long?

38:04.633 --> 38:07.967
Three years at least.
They want a commitment.

38:07.967 --> 38:09.667
What about Ash Park?

38:09.667 --> 38:11.300
We'd get in a manager.

38:11.300 --> 38:12.367
Roy's here.

38:12.367 --> 38:15.233
Harry would help,
given what we've done.

38:19.200 --> 38:21.533
It would be wonderful for David.

38:21.533 --> 38:22.600
It would.

38:22.600 --> 38:24.733
-I'd love it.
-[ Laughing ] I know.

38:25.733 --> 38:29.167
But I don't want to make
a false start here.

38:29.167 --> 38:31.333
The timing's appalling.

38:32.667 --> 38:34.767
Well, we wouldn't have to
take off immediately.

38:38.167 --> 38:39.667
So?

38:39.667 --> 38:42.667
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

38:42.667 --> 38:45.067
A few days ago, yes.

38:46.667 --> 38:48.200
Today...

38:49.733 --> 38:51.833
...I'm not so sure.

38:53.800 --> 38:56.333
[ Mid-tempo music playing ]

39:02.833 --> 39:05.400
Zelda's mumsy has been too dear
about us.

39:05.400 --> 39:07.467
We're so lucky
when so many get rejected.

39:07.467 --> 39:09.533
"It's better than being left
on the shelf."

39:09.533 --> 39:12.767
That's what she said,
the darling.

39:12.767 --> 39:15.067
Better Sappho than solo,
it seems.

39:17.867 --> 39:19.600
-Who are you expecting?
-Oh, I know.

39:19.600 --> 39:21.600
He can't keep his eye
from the door.

39:21.600 --> 39:23.600
A new fella?
Tell.

39:23.600 --> 39:24.967
No.

39:25.467 --> 39:26.667
Just Harry Polson.

39:27.700 --> 39:29.167
Adorable Harry?

39:29.167 --> 39:30.567
You're not stuck on him?

39:30.567 --> 39:31.400
No.

39:31.400 --> 39:33.067
[ Laughs ]

39:33.067 --> 39:34.400
He's not my type.

39:34.400 --> 39:36.167
Says he,
madly watching the door.

39:36.167 --> 39:39.067
More like you're not his,
if he's a no-show.

39:39.067 --> 39:41.500
You always take it too far.

39:42.600 --> 39:45.133
[ Music continues ]

39:52.700 --> 39:54.633
If all the world were like this.

39:54.633 --> 39:56.833
Stranger, but truer.

39:57.333 --> 40:00.533
He was wondering if I had
any ideas for radio serials.

40:00.533 --> 40:01.933
He's a producer.

40:01.933 --> 40:06.533
No judgment, no "you're too
scandalous to be employed."

40:06.533 --> 40:08.667
I was thinking "Tender Vines."

40:08.667 --> 40:09.667
You tore it up.

40:09.667 --> 40:11.800
Mm.
It's all in here.

40:11.800 --> 40:15.200
And I'm ready to face it now,
finally.

40:15.200 --> 40:16.433
Good.

40:20.000 --> 40:21.867
[ Music continues ]

40:22.467 --> 40:24.500
You know I love you.

40:25.633 --> 40:26.500
Same.

40:27.433 --> 40:29.267
We will make
superlative parents.

40:29.267 --> 40:32.300
Who needs marriage?
We're trailblazers.

40:32.300 --> 40:36.367
Oh, brave new world
that has such people in it.

40:37.533 --> 40:41.633
I'll go find Prudence
and she can show you the plans.

40:44.300 --> 40:46.500
We're hiring Prudence
for publicity.

40:46.500 --> 40:48.700
She's been marvelous.

40:49.367 --> 40:52.633
-They're nice together.
-Mm-hmm.

40:52.633 --> 40:55.533
They'll make it work
in their own way.

40:55.533 --> 40:57.233
Like you.

40:59.233 --> 41:01.367
You're managing a good face.

41:01.367 --> 41:04.700
Ah.
Who wants frowns?

41:04.700 --> 41:07.200
If it all gets too much.

41:10.500 --> 41:12.667
[ Laughs ]

41:12.667 --> 41:15.467
I just might.

41:15.467 --> 41:16.967
Possibly.

41:16.967 --> 41:19.167
[ Music continues ]

41:21.467 --> 41:24.067
[ Clock ticking,
footsteps approaching ]

41:25.067 --> 41:27.100
You sure you don't want to come?

41:27.100 --> 41:29.667
I am happily ensconced here.

41:29.667 --> 41:32.667
I'll live vicariously
through your tales.

41:33.133 --> 41:34.600
-Coward.
-[ Chuckles ]

41:36.233 --> 41:37.933
I can't wait to tell her.

41:37.933 --> 41:39.433
We still make a good team.

41:41.167 --> 41:42.667
I'm getting you back
on the board.

41:42.667 --> 41:43.833
[ Exhales sharply ]

41:43.833 --> 41:46.067
Sir Richard wouldn't know
what struck him.

41:46.633 --> 41:49.233
No. It depends what I do
with this place.

41:49.233 --> 41:50.967
Are we any closer to a decision?

41:51.833 --> 41:53.900
I think so.

41:53.900 --> 41:57.900
One partly inspired by you
and partly by Douglas.

42:00.800 --> 42:02.667
When I'm more sure of it myself.

42:03.800 --> 42:05.167
Go.

42:11.333 --> 42:13.700
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

42:15.333 --> 42:17.867
[ Dog barking in distance ]

42:34.100 --> 42:36.367
[ Music continues ]

42:56.967 --> 43:02.133
The thing I dread most...
is losing control.

43:03.367 --> 43:05.833
From the minute I entered
Ravensbruck, I had none.

43:05.833 --> 43:08.400
And leaving,
I vowed never to lose it again.

43:10.267 --> 43:15.800
That is my greatest fear --
losing control.

43:15.800 --> 43:19.167
And it's time I faced it.

43:23.900 --> 43:25.900
Evens we stay.

43:26.700 --> 43:27.933
Odds we go.

43:29.267 --> 43:31.400
-No.
-Submitting to chance.

43:31.400 --> 43:33.567
-Sarah --
-I have to.

43:35.533 --> 43:37.067
I have to.

43:38.267 --> 43:39.833
Are you sure?

43:42.833 --> 43:45.067
And I'm not scared.

43:51.500 --> 43:53.533
[ Die rattles ]

43:55.167 --> 43:57.667
[ Music continues ]

43:57.667 --> 43:59.067
Well.

44:00.567 --> 44:01.900
Well.

44:04.300 --> 44:07.100
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

44:07.100 --> 44:13.733
* When no one else
can understand me *

44:13.733 --> 44:18.967
* When everything I do
is wrong *

44:20.600 --> 44:26.367
* You give me love
and consolation *

44:27.067 --> 44:32.467
* You give me hope to carry on *

44:32.467 --> 44:39.067
* And you try to show your love
for me *

44:39.067 --> 44:45.600
* In everything you do *

44:45.600 --> 44:49.267
* That's the wonder *

44:50.700 --> 44:56.667
* The wonder of you *

45:00.067 --> 45:04.967
* And when you smile,
the world is brighter *

45:06.667 --> 45:11.067
* You touch my hand,
and I'm a king *

45:13.100 --> 45:17.800
* Your kiss to me
is worth a fortune *

45:19.733 --> 45:24.933
* Your love for me
is everything *

45:24.933 --> 45:31.700
* And you're always there
to lend a hand *

45:31.700 --> 45:38.200
* In all I try to do *

45:38.200 --> 45:43.267
* That's the wonder *

45:43.267 --> 45:48.967
* The wonder of you *

45:50.900 --> 45:54.833
* Guess I'll never know *

45:54.833 --> 46:04.533
* The reason why you love me
as you do *

46:04.533 --> 46:10.333
* That's the wonder *

46:10.333 --> 46:21.400
* The wonder of you *

